            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>No. Google shows extensions only when it predicts they'll improve ad performance based on context, device, ad position, and other signals. Your ad generally needs to be in the top positions for extensions to appear.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Why did Google rename ad extensions to assets?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Google renamed them in 2022 to unify vocabulary across Search, Display, YouTube, and Performance Max. The mechanic is the same — supplemental elements that expand the ad — but 'asset' better fits campaigns where ad copy is machine-assembled.</p></div></div>
